> It's a disaster so far.

A good-looking alternative (if we can't or don't want to use IPsec) is
OpenVPN, <http://openvpn.sourceforge.net/>. Uses UDP for tunneling, so
should be able to cope even when the ISP firewalls IPsec packets (eg, if
VPN is against their TOS for residential accounts).

